-- Slovenia Leads 10-Man Algeria 1-0 in 2nd Half of World Cup Group Game
-- Peter-Joseph Hegarty
-- 2010-06-13T13:09:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/slovenia-leads-10-man-algeria-1-0-in-2nd-half-of-world-cup-group-game.html

          
          
             Slovenia leads Algeria 1-0 after 80
minutes of their World Cup Group C game in Polokwane. Robert
Koren got the goal in the 79th minute.  
 Earlier, Abdelkader Ghezzal of Algeria was red-carded for a
second yellow card.  
 England drew 1-1 with the U.S. in the same group yesterday.  
 Later today Serbia plays Ghana and Germany meets Australia,
both in Group D.  
          
          


  


        